BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2uAeX9G7v_fn5koLVfJPg
SUMMARY:Tour De Pints
DTSTAMP:20260413T004141Z
DTSTART:20260509T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join the throng of around 100 riders on a looping route through
	 North Seattle neighborhoods - Fremont\, Ballard\, Greenwood\, Ravena\, an
	d more. The route is still a secret but will be announced shortly before t
	he ride!The Tour De Pints is Seattle's biggest bike and brew ride since 20
	11. We'll take a safe route that avoids busy car roads as much as possible
	 and suitable for all skill levels. You can't avoid North Seattle hills th
	ough so be ready for just a bit of that!We'll visit five breweries - some 
	old route favorites (it wouldn't be a Tour De Pints without Flying Bike!) 
	and some new places we've never had on the route before. The route is roug
	hly a 20 mile loop\, starting at a different brewery near where it begins!
	Swag raffles will take place at each brewery with the biggest and best pri
	zes saved for the final location!Sign up at TourDePints.com\n\nFrom Seattl
	e Beer Week
LOCATION:Location ID: 3dbf88ff-8af6-4e33-ad12-3f9f8d99e0b6
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:beer-week
CATEGORIES:Seattle Beer Week
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kJ_ZMignpM_YWNcsfZdgS
SUMMARY:Seattle Vs. Olympia Hot Dog Relay Throwdown
DTSTAMP:20260413T004141Z
DTSTART:20260509T203000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us at Halcyon Brewing for our 2nd annual Hot Dog Relay Thr
	owdown as we pit 3 Seattle breweries (Halcyon\, Big Time and Ladd &amp\; L
	ass) vs. 3 Olympia breweries (Ilk\, 3 Magnets and Well 80. In addition to 
	the brewers competition\, consumers can enter the competition with teams o
	f 3. The winners will receive a be-jewelled belt a multitude of schwag and
	 gift cards. Competition format: Teams of 3 and each person needs to consu
	me one hot dog and drink one pint of beer before the next person goes. The
	 fastest team wins.\n\nFrom Seattle Beer Week
LOCATION:Location ID: m9stfl7e
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:beer-week
CATEGORIES:Seattle Beer Week
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7niYbvV3Z039YP1Vd0pla
SUMMARY:Pine Box Beer Can Derby
DTSTAMP:20260413T004141Z
DTSTART:20260509T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:The race is on! Come &amp\; try your luck racing cans cub scout
	 style down the tracks to beer glory. Join us at 3pm to purchase a beer\, 
	canned of course\, &amp\; a race kit. We’ll race in heats starting at 5pm 
	w/ prizes for 1st\, 2nd\, &amp\; 3rd + most attractive car! Tools will be 
	provided. Cub scout gear encouraged! See you at the starting line.3pm to 5
	pm - Build Time&nbsp\;5pm - RACE TIME!!ALL CARS MUST PASS INSPECTION TO QU
	ALIFY FOR THE RACE Following are the inspection points&nbsp\;1. The can we
	ight shall not exceed 5.0 ounces. The official race scale shall be conside
	red final.&nbsp\;2. The overall length of the can shall not exceed 7 inche
	s.&nbsp\;3. The overall width of the can shall not exceed 2 ¾ inches.&nbsp
	\;4. The can must have 1 ¾” clearance between the wheels.&nbsp\;5. The can
	 must have 3/8” clearance underneath the body.&nbsp\;6. The can may be sha
	ped any way that is desired.&nbsp\;7. The can must be freewheeling\, with 
	no starting devices.&nbsp\;8. You must use official Pine Box Wheels and Ax
	les\, YOUR CAN CAR MUST BE BUILT ON SITE.Each can must pass inspection by 
	the official inspection committee &nbsp\;before it will be allowed to comp
	ete. The Inspection Committee has the &nbsp\;responsibility to disqualify 
	those cans that do not meet these &nbsp\;specifications.Hosted by New Belg
	ium Brewing\n\nFrom Seattle Beer Week
LOCATION:Location ID: m7279q0m
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:beer-week
CATEGORIES:Seattle Beer Week
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
